npm  → Manager

npx  → Executor

More precisely:

npm

Installs, manages and runs packages that belong to your project.

Examples:

npm install fastify

npm install react

npm run dev

Think:

"I want this package to become part of my project."

npx

Executes a package, usually for one-time tasks.

Examples:

npx create-vite@latest

npx prisma init

npx tsc --init

Think:

"I just want to use this tool right now."

